00:40:22,621 --> 00:40:23,861
the film roll must be finished.

568
00:40:24,270 --> 00:40:25,552
It's okay if it's finished.

569
00:40:25,709 --> 00:40:27,150
I've taken pictures of everyone.

570
00:40:28,107 --> 00:40:29,400
Have you counted yourself?

571
00:40:30,231 --> 00:40:32,450
Oh, I forgot to count.

572
00:40:32,475 --> 00:40:33,917
Come on, I'll take one for you.

573
00:40:35,392 --> 00:40:36,427
Why?

574
00:40:36,886 --> 00:40:38,846
Didn't you like the one
I took for you last time?

575
00:40:39,308 --> 00:40:40,388
I liked it.

576
00:40:42,092 --> 00:40:43,252
Then let's take one together.

577
00:40:43,783 --> 00:40:44,783
Sure.

578
00:40:51,385 --> 00:40:53,187
1, 2, 3.

579
00:40:54,724 --> 00:40:55,944
One more picture.

580
00:40:59,376 --> 00:41:00,516
1, 2, 3.

581
00:41:02,558 --> 00:41:03,645
Oh.

582
00:41:04,033 --> 00:41:05,140
Nut.

583
00:41:10,969 --> 00:41:12,049
What are you doing?

584
00:41:12,552 --> 00:41:14,372
Continuing the song from yesterday.

585
00:41:14,905 --> 00:41:15,905
Want to help?

586
00:41:16,465 --> 00:41:17,679
I've written up to here.

587
00:41:31,891 --> 00:41:33,140
Boo!

588
00:41:33,523 --> 00:41:34,992
You scared me.

589
00:41:35,016 --> 00:41:37,160
What would you do if I
died of a heart attack?

590
00:41:38,767 --> 00:41:40,653
You won't die that easily.

591
00:41:40,677 --> 00:41:42,726
You'll live until you're 40.

592
00:41:44,291 --> 00:41:46,694
Next time, make some noise
when you show up, old man.

593
00:41:47,060 --> 00:41:48,086
Who's an old man?

594
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:50,748
You are, Uncle Win.

595
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:54,694
You got me, I can't even argue.

596
00:42:00,821 --> 00:42:02,772
Hey, can I ask you something?

597
00:42:14,052 --> 00:42:15,580
In the next 20 years,

598
00:42:15,604 --> 00:42:16,959
Lin and Nut...

599
00:42:17,353 --> 00:42:18,459
I already told you.

600
00:42:19,333 --> 00:42:21,588
That you'll find out when the time comes.

601
00:42:22,725 --> 00:42:24,815
Damn, if it were me,

602
00:42:24,839 --> 00:42:26,159
I would have told you everything.

603
00:42:26,502 --> 00:42:27,848
Why are you holding back?

604
00:42:37,229 --> 00:42:38,276
Win, Win.

605
00:42:58,263 --> 00:43:00,016
Haven't you guys packed up yet?

606
00:43:00,604 --> 00:43:02,404
I have to play at the
bar later this evening.

607
00:43:02,836 --> 00:43:04,392
If you're slow, I'm not waiting.

608
00:43:05,240 --> 00:43:06,384
Yeah, I'll pack up quickly.

609
00:43:07,297 --> 00:43:08,677
Listen to this song first.

610
00:43:08,816 --> 00:43:10,096
Lin helped me write it just now.

611
00:43:10,479 --> 00:43:11,546
Okay.

612
00:43:20,331 --> 00:43:21,746
♪ Still cool. ♪

613
00:43:21,771 --> 00:43:25,166
♪ Even if you leave, I'll still be okay. ♪

614
00:43:25,190 --> 00:43:26,850
♪ It's probably fine. ♪

615
00:43:26,875 --> 00:43:31,755
♪ I tell everyone that I'm okay. ♪

616
00:43:34,180 --> 00:43:35,908
♪ But every night, ♪

617
00:43:35,932 --> 00:43:39,513
♪ I just keep thinking about you. ♪

618
00:43:39,580 --> 00:43:41,410
♪ I don't eat, I don't sleep. ♪

619
00:43:41,441 --> 00:43:44,189
♪ Oh, would you know, ♪

620
00:43:44,213 --> 00:43:46,266
♪ I feel like I'm about to die. ♪

621
00:43:48,913 --> 00:43:50,823
♪ Acting too tough, ♪

622
00:43:50,847 --> 00:43:53,157
♪ my mouth doesn't match my heart. ♪

623
00:43:53,195 --> 00:43:56,078
♪ In the end, there are only tears. ♪

624
00:43:56,212 --> 00:43:57,962
♪ Where are you now? ♪

625
00:43:57,986 --> 00:44:03,836
♪ Can you please come back to me? ♪

626
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:11,318
♪ You know I can't be alone. ♪

627
00:44:11,343 --> 00:44:14,744
♪ I just talk big like that. ♪

628
00:44:14,769 --> 00:44:18,252
♪ When you're not
here, I don't act tough. ♪

629
00:44:18,358 --> 00:44:22,586
♪ Okay, I give up,
without any conditions. ♪

630
00:44:22,612 --> 00:44:23,892
♪ It's probably only you ♪

631
00:44:23,916 --> 00:44:26,087
♪ who can beat me at everything. ♪

632
00:44:26,112 --> 00:44:27,791
♪ Okay, I give up. ♪

633
00:44:27,815 --> 00:44:29,681
♪ I won't act tough anymore. ♪

634
00:44:29,705 --> 00:44:32,519
♪ I just want you, my dear... ♪

635
00:44:32,952 --> 00:44:35,225
♪ to come back. ♪

636
00:44:39,754 --> 00:44:40,934
Very beautiful.

637
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:41,734
Thank you.

638
00:44:41,759 --> 00:44:42,891
I've been writing for so long

639
00:44:42,915 --> 00:44:44,184
and it's not even this good.

640
00:44:45,673 --> 00:44:48,731
Well, you wrote it well from the beginning.

641
00:44:49,471 --> 00:44:50,664
Sweet talker.

642
00:44:51,417 --> 00:44:53,383
See? I told you it's not a sad song.

643
00:44:53,407 --> 00:44:54,358
It's a love song.

644
00:44:54,382 --> 00:44:55,650
Do you understand now?

645
00:44:56,065 --> 00:44:56,878
I understand now.

646
00:44:56,903 --> 00:44:57,903
Awesome.

647
00:44:58,153 --> 00:44:59,373
Very good.

648
00:44:59,398 --> 00:45:00,532
What does everyone think?

649
00:45:01,005 --> 00:45:03,085
If it's okay, I'll continue
writing the second half.

650
00:45:04,758 --> 00:45:05,772
I think...

651
00:45:08,055 --> 00:45:09,248
it's so beautiful.

652
00:45:11,420 --> 00:45:13,131
Let's use this song for the final round.

653
00:45:16,877 --> 00:45:19,429
I think we'll definitely be the champions.

654
00:45:19,669 --> 00:45:20,669
Don't you think so?

655
00:45:22,464 --> 00:45:23,984
It's very beautiful.

656
00:45:44,042 --> 00:45:44,950
Win.

657
00:45:44,975 --> 00:45:46,482
What is it, Lin?

658
00:45:47,770 --> 00:45:48,770
Well,

659
00:45:49,526 --> 00:45:51,246
I have something to consult with you about.

660
00:45:53,317 --> 00:45:54,317
Sure.

661
00:45:56,320 --> 00:45:57,450
I think...

662
00:45:58,473 --> 00:45:59,693
I like Nut.

663
00:46:02,184 --> 00:46:03,804
I want to confess my love.

664
00:46:05,277 --> 00:46:07,170
Can you help me find the right moment?

665
00:46:13,598 --> 00:46:15,887
Can you just play continuously?

666
00:46:15,955 --> 00:46:16,816
Yes.

667
00:46:16,841 --> 00:46:18,694
One song, and let it run continuously.

668
00:46:25,890 --> 00:46:27,083
Of course, Lin.

669
00:47:04,325 --> 00:47:06,005
(Next Episode)
Are you not free these days?

670
00:47:06,302 --> 00:47:08,622
I haven't eaten your stir-fried
vegetables in a long time.

671
00:47:08,699 --> 00:47:10,750
Nut, I have something to tell you.

672
00:47:11,411 --> 00:47:12,532
Are you okay?

673
00:47:12,789 --> 00:47:14,064
You seem distracted.

674
00:47:14,315 --> 00:47:16,381
Today, I feel like Win is
too stressed, don't you?

675
00:47:16,876 --> 00:47:18,690
Do you know what's wrong with Win?

676
00:47:26,685 --> 00:47:28,738
How could you let me be a fool like this?

677
00:47:30,162 --> 00:47:30,950
Hello, ma'am.

678
00:47:30,975 --> 00:47:32,183
I don't think it's convenient for you

679
00:47:32,207 --> 00:47:34,074
to use the rehearsal room here anymore.

680
00:47:35,681 --> 00:47:38,983
♪ We went through tough times together. ♪

681
00:47:39,008 --> 00:47:44,345
♪ You stood in the rain with me. ♪

682
00:47:44,822 --> 00:47:49,201
♪ On the day I had no one left. ♪

683
00:47:49,265 --> 00:47:52,532
♪ No matter how many
years pass, it's still you. ♪

684
00:47:52,557 --> 00:47:55,997
♪ No matter how long, it has to be you. ♪

685
00:47:56,022 --> 00:47:58,797
♪ If it's not you... ♪

686
00:47:58,822 --> 00:48:03,042
♪ I wouldn't want to get
through the bad times. ♪

687
00:48:03,067 --> 00:48:06,220
♪ I will remember your name. ♪

688
00:48:06,245 --> 00:48:11,294
♪ No matter how tonight ends. ♪

689
00:48:11,805 --> 00:48:18,106
♪ Everything that's
happened has been worth it. ♪
